Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.52,0:00:04.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go, to the hospital!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.06,0:00:06.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.86,0:00:10.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go to the hospital so they can treat you and you can get better.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.07,0:00:12.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You promised to tell me, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.86,0:00:14.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The answer to your deduction!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.37,0:00:17.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.03,0:00:20.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because maybe I have a feeling that...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.12,0:00:24.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I agree with your reasoning...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.29,0:00:26.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.00,0:00:28.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why, until you go to the hospital...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.38,0:00:32.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not letting go of your hand, never!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.64,0:00:36.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin'ichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.39,0:00:42.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A desperate crisis...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.10,0:00:44.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A splendid revival reverses the conclusion to a case!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.39,0:00:46.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The terms of the engagement are "No Smoking!"...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.06,0:00:47.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And yet, for reasons unknown, there's a huge explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.40,0:00:49.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.98,0:00:51.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.86,0:00:53.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.38,0:02:39.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.80,0:02:41.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wake up, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.22,0:02:46.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.35,0:02:48.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.06,0:02:50.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is your cold all right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.94,0:02:57.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and the others headed to the airport in\NMouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s car so they could get back to Osaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.90,0:02:59.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.36,0:03:01.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.62,0:03:04.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you let go of my hand sometime soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.37,0:03:09.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I'm sorry. Did it hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.46,0:03:10.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.58,0:03:12.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that's funny...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.17,0:03:16.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought I was holding onto Shin'ichi's hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.80,0:03:18.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I suddenly felt faint...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.38,0:03:22.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because I shot you with the spare tranquilizer gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.76,0:03:25.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess it's because you were really tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.72,0:03:27.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You kept holding onto his hand the entire time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.60,0:03:32.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even when Shin'ichi was carrying you and putting you in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.19,0:03:36.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's Shin'ichi? Did he go in my dad's car also?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.82,0:03:41.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, he rested in my car for a bit until he was feeling better.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.45,0:03:45.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He left saying he had some unfinished case to tidy up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.08,0:03:49.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, he shook himself free of my hand and left?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.33,0:03:50.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That mystery-loving prince of fools.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.54,0:03:52.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Prince of fools?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.00,0:03:54.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that's too bad...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.79,0:03:58.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was so determined not to let go of his hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.51,0:04:01.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.01,0:04:05.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take a good look at the left side of Kudo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s sweater.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.47,0:04:10.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See how it's been cut from the cuff all the way\Nto the hem and sealed with safety pins?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.35,0:04:15.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That proves he put on the sweater while\Nyou were still holding his left hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.90,0:04:19.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As such, you really have nothing to regret.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.82,0:04:25.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh no. Is your cold coming back?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.53,0:04:28.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm fine. I'm fine...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.58,0:04:40.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it was thanks to that little girl putting the girl from\Nthe detective agency to sleep with the tranquilizer gun...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.80,0:04:46.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That you weren't found out in the end, even though\Nyou shrank in the car while still holding hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.97,0:04:50.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Holding hands? Who told you that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.43,0:04:53.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That old man, Agasa, told me over the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.02,0:04:56.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Professor... Keep your mouth shut...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.31,0:05:00.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, you did get some of it, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.40,0:05:02.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The drug that changes you back?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.36,0:05:06.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd be better if you had that drug with\Nyou, just in case it becomes necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.28,0:05:09.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's what I thought, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.74,0:05:14.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, didn't I just tell you guys not to eavesdrop?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.96,0:05:15.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Kudo...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.62,0:05:18.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, sorry. Ignore that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.58,0:05:21.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're all on the way to go camping.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.59,0:05:26.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So then, how did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.68,0:05:32.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I asked Haibara to give me a hundred tablets of that drug to start with.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.10,0:05:34.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A hundred?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.56,0:05:35.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.77,0:05:38.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think even that much will be enough though.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.98,0:05:40.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm warning you now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.94,0:05:45.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Each time you take the drug, your body builds up more resistance to it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.07,0:05:46.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it grows less effective.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.20,0:05:50.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I truly don't know if you'll be able to return to your former body.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.87,0:05:57.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, since you want to act cool for that girl at the detective agency...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.67,0:06:00.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You might not even last a week, even with a hundred.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.67,0:06:03.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like she needed to tell me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.71,0:06:04.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, Kudo...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.46,0:06:07.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though the little girl tells you not to...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.13,0:06:12.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it be better if you tell the girl at\Nthe detective agency the whole story?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.39,0:06:15.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That way you can confess your love sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.89,0:06:17.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.69,0:06:18.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.44,0:06:21.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's exactly why I can't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.36,0:06:23.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What can't you do (ika-nai)?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.98,0:06:26.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't go (ika-nee) camping with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.78,0:06:28.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no... it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.36,0:06:33.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot! We're going camping in the mountains.\NThere's no way there'll be a squid (ika) there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.58,0:06:38.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what you're talking about on the phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.71,0:06:42.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no, I've already finished talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.88,0:06:44.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey! Wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.92,0:06:48.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He hung up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.51,0:06:50.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.14,0:06:53.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is going to be fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.93,0:06:55.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The campground we're going to, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.81,0:06:56.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.77,0:06:59.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard it has really beautiful scenery.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.98,0:07:03.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, what should we have for dinner tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.36,0:07:05.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bought lots of ingredients.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.61,0:07:07.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, I want a barbecue!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.61,0:07:09.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You always want that, Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.40,0:07:11.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What would you like, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.57,0:07:13.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The usual - curry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.49,0:07:15.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about you, Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.91,0:07:19.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't matter. If I were in the mood to eat, anything would be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.21,0:07:23.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, don't pay attention to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.00,0:07:26.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems she's been like this since this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.30,0:07:29.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet she's worrying about something silly again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.73,0:07:42.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me the engine died again!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.44,0:07:47.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you have it checked before we left?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.02,0:07:50.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, and thanks to that, the engine's running perfectly...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.49,0:07:54.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, as for the gasoline, we're out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.08,0:07:58.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, it's getting dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.49,0:08:01.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'd better hurry and call someone to bring us some gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.79,0:08:02.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.75,0:08:05.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think so too. That's why I'm calling him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.54,0:08:06.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.67,0:08:13.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember, the person who's been living next door to\Nme since that incident with the fire - Okiya Subaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.51,0:08:17.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since he said he'd be relaxing at home all day today...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.81,0:08:20.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wouldn't mind spending two hours coming out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.31,0:08:23.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? We're out of the cellphone service range here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.27,0:08:25.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What'll we do!?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.90,0:08:27.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here in the middle of the mountains!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.77,0:08:31.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're still pretty far from the campground, aren't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.19,0:08:34.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For now, we have three choices.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.78,0:08:42.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Walk back to the gasoline stand we passed by\Naround thirty minutes ago, and buy some gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.29,0:08:50.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stay here and wait until a car happens by, and\Nthen ask them to take us to the gasoline stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.63,0:08:51.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Otherwise...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.09,0:08:56.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We go to that villa viewable on the mountain\Nabove and ask to borrow their phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.93,0:09:02.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it'd take us more than two hours\Nto get back to the gas stand on foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.14,0:09:08.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since we haven't seen many cars pass by\Non this mountain road, it'd be tough to wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.27,0:09:14.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, I think the safest bet is to\Nhead to that villa while it's still light out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.11,0:09:16.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a beautiful house.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.70,0:09:18.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's like a princess lives there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.95,0:09:21.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder if they'll serve us food when we get there?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.95,0:09:24.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We may get a full course of French cooking!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.37,0:09:26.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want Italian!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.58,0:09:29.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought you came to go camping.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.38,0:09:40.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop, stop, stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.89,0:09:46.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.94,0:09:52.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm terribly sorry, but could you take us to a nearby gasoline stand?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.07,0:09:56.78,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Sudou Gouki (34)\NIT Company President
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.40,0:09:54.82,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I don't mind, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.94,0:09:56.78,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Could you give me a few more details?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.20,0:10:01.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The thing is, we were on our way to a campground...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.66,0:10:03.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And happened to run out of gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.20,0:10:08.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since we're out of cellphone range, we're in a quandary.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.75,0:10:11.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, so that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.38,0:10:12.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.09,0:10:15.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait here until you die!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.26,0:10:16.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You old goat!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.89,0:10:26.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.56,0:10:27.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What an unpleasant person!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.89,0:10:29.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's the worst!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.73,0:10:34.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, we may well have to beg for help\Nfrom that unpleasant fellow once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.24,0:10:37.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.99,0:10:40.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That car was one that has ridiculously high maintenance costs...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.95,0:10:43.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A classic car that rich people prefer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.62,0:10:45.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person driving a car like that around here...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.37,0:10:52.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Might just be the same rich person who built\Nthis luxury villa in the middle of these mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.88,0:10:53.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.09,0:10:57.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, let's not ask him!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.01,0:10:58.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.30,0:11:02.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd rather wait here until another car\Ncomes than ask someone like him!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.76,0:11:08.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, there's a chance that guy wasn't going to\Nthe villa, but to a completely different place.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.60,0:11:12.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't be a bad idea to go and check, would it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.48,0:11:14.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.06,0:11:17.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's leave the luggage in the car and go together to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.57,0:11:19.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, if we all ask together...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.07,0:11:23.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, we should at least take a flashlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.28,0:11:25.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is getting dark, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.37,0:11:29.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's in the pocket beneath the driver's seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.00,0:11:29.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you get it for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.71,0:11:31.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.59,0:11:37.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with you? You're acting like a queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.92,0:11:39.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that what it looks like?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.72,0:11:42.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know what's gotten into you, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.64,0:11:44.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While we're camping...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.10,0:11:49.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An explosion?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.52,0:11:56.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.98,0:11:59.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The emblem from that guy's car!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.82,0:12:02.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.78,0:12:04.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.12,0:12:06.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it was the same car as before...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.78,0:12:08.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did it explode?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.70,0:12:10.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was the bomb planted on it from the beginning?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.37,0:12:16.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, was the reason he didn't give us a ride because\Nhe didn't want us to be caught in the explosion?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.92,0:12:19.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be. It didn't seem that way at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.89,0:12:27.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gouki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.06,0:12:29.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop, Ena! It's dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.22,0:12:32.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But... But...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.06,0:12:34.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I called for a fire truck and an ambulance!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.06,0:12:38.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, did that Gouki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.07,0:12:45.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did he have dyed brown hair, a beard, and wear\Na black fleece jacket over a wool sweatshirt?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.78,0:12:47.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who... are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.62,0:12:52.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A man like that, driving a classic car, passed us on the road a bit ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.38,0:13:05.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The deceased was Sudou Gouki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, age 34.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.39,0:13:12.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems he was a company president who made a ton of money\Nfrom his IT business, which let him build this gorgeous villa.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.43,0:13:16.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cause of the fire was a cigarette he was smoking.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.19,0:13:17.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A cigarette he was smoking?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.56,0:13:22.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, a plastic container in the garage with\Ngasoline inside had accidentally tipped over...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.03,0:13:26.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which ended up filling the garage with gasoline fumes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.32,0:13:31.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, Sudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} arrived in his car\Nand opened the door of the garage...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.12,0:13:38.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was smoking inside the stopped car, and in\Nthe moment he stepped out, the fire erupted.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.54,0:13:41.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fire completely engulfed the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.96,0:13:45.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We found a burnt cigarette butt, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.34,0:13:46.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.93,0:13:49.93,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Ginbayashi Ena (31)\NSudou's Fiancee
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.34,0:13:49.93,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Gouki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said he had quit smoking!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.43,0:13:52.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hate cigarettes, so he did it for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.89,0:13:54.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm - who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.89,0:13:57.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's Sudou's fiancee, Ginbayashi Ena{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.69,0:14:03.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the weekends, everyone usually gets together here for parties.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.23,0:14:06.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tonight, Sudou was supposed to announce something.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.24,0:14:08.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our wedding.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.70,0:14:11.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'd finally decided on the day for our wedding.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.62,0:14:15.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he was planning to announce it to everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.00,0:14:19.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then... and then... why did this have to happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.09,0:14:24.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, since we found a burnt marriage license...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.67,0:14:27.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What you're saying appears to be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.26,0:14:30.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But as for giving up smoking, it looks like that was a lie, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.76,0:14:36.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ashtray in that car had a large number of cigarette butts in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.27,0:14:40.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And next to the body, in addition to the burnt cigarette...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.02,0:14:46.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'd dropped a bag that contained a\Nsealed carton of cigarettes and a lighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.78,0:14:47.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.53,0:14:51.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I was just telling him to stop smoking a little while ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.57,0:14:52.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A little while ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.03,0:14:59.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got a phone call from Gouki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} about\Nan hour ago that said he was on his way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.96,0:15:02.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,During that call, Ena told him...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.50,0:15:06.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"If you don't quit smoking, then our engagement is off!"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.34,0:15:09.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was that phone call really from Sudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.47,0:15:10.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.38,0:15:12.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was the one who answered the phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.18,0:15:14.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I talked with him before hanging up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.51,0:15:17.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So not only did Sudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} not quit smoking...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.10,0:15:21.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He ignored the recommended way to store\Ngasoline, and used a plastic container.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.15,0:15:23.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess Sudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} suffered the consequences...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.52,0:15:25.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And died in an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.90,0:15:28.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, we can't say that for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.15,0:15:28.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.11,0:15:33.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because, if Sudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} got out of the\Ncar with a cigarette in his mouth...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.49,0:15:37.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means he took the cigarette out and\Nlit it shortly before he got out, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.70,0:15:40.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yet it isn't here anywhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.50,0:15:43.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The open cigarette pack, I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.75,0:15:47.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Mr. Forensics guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.84,0:15:49.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,l-ls that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.42,0:15:53.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we couldn't find it in the car, the garage, or anywhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.43,0:15:55.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why isn't it here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.47,0:16:02.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That cigarette butt might have been thrown in the\Ngarage before Sudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} arrived, might it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.52,0:16:04.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.36,0:16:08.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.15,0:16:09.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please explain!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.94,0:16:13.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I mean this wasn't just an accident, but\Nwas probably planned by someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.16,0:16:16.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It may have been murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.70,0:16:18.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure, Conan?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.62,0:16:24.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the polyethylene tank placed in the garage had tipped over...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.17,0:16:29.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The gasoline vaporized and filled the garage.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.00,0:16:32.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whereupon Sudou Gouki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} brought his car inside the garage.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.09,0:16:39.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He stopped the car and the instance he got out\Nwith a cigarette in his mouth, it exploded.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.93,0:16:46.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They even found the cigarette butt\Nthat caused the fire inside the garage.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.48,0:16:50.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At first glance, it appears to just be an accident, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.28,0:16:56.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they can't find the open cigarette pack the victim\Nsupposedly took the cigarette from anywhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.57,0:17:03.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then that means the cigarette butt had already\Nbeen in the garage before Sudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.46,0:17:11.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means it may be a fake piece of evidence that the culprit\Nleft in order to make it look like an accidental death.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.84,0:17:14.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amazing, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.55,0:17:16.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well done!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.30,0:17:17.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.10,0:17:21.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've been investigating the garage for some time, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.01,0:17:24.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We haven't found anything that looked like a detonator.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.48,0:17:29.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Sudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't have a cigarette case or anything either, did he?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.27,0:17:30.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.82,0:17:32.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's definitely strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.86,0:17:35.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet if you search more, you'll find something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.49,0:17:37.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the last one.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.82,0:17:41.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That cigarette was the last one.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.95,0:17:47.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So couldn't he have thrown the empty pack out\Nthe car window before he went into the garage?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.62,0:17:54.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gouki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} always used to crumple empty\Ncigarette packs into a ball and do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.42,0:18:00.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, are you saying that if we search around\Nthe villa, we'll find that empty pack?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.76,0:18:01.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.97,0:18:05.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, but he may have thrown the empty pack out a long time ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.48,0:18:10.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Gouki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had lied about quitting smoking...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.15,0:18:13.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you think he'd avoid throwing it out around the villa?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.90,0:18:18.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's true, it would expand the field of\Nsearch greatly, making it difficult to find.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.11,0:18:21.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention the deep valley along the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.70,0:18:24.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that's all I can think of...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.91,0:18:26.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Miss...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.54,0:18:30.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you really believe that Sudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had quit smoking?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.75,0:18:35.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you had found out that he was secretly smoking...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.88,0:18:39.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You would have only had to drop the plastic\Ngasoline tanks inside the garage and...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.47,0:18:40.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.72,0:18:44.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nobody's noticed Sudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} secretly smoking!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.68,0:18:45.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.72,0:18:48.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He never smoked a single cigarette since said he was quitting!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.35,0:18:52.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that was just in front of you guys, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.86,0:18:55.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We met Sudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} a little while ago, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.49,0:18:58.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was a brazen liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.86,0:19:03.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I thought his fiancee might know about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.20,0:19:05.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brazen liar?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.95,0:19:06.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.87,0:19:10.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We had run out of gas on our way to a campground...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.12,0:19:14.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So we stopped Sudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who happened\Nto be passing by on the same road.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.88,0:19:18.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We asked him to take us to the gasoline stand, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.84,0:19:20.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when he was real mean!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.63,0:19:23.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we went over by the driver's seat and explained the situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.76,0:19:26.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At first that guy said "Get on in," but then...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.81,0:19:28.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He swore at us and drove away.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.89,0:19:32.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait here until you die, you old goat!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.19,0:19:35.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, that's terrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.15,0:19:38.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't want to speak ill of the dead, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.82,0:19:42.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't seem like the kind of person who\Nwould keep a promise to quit smoking.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.12,0:19:46.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That does sound like something he would say.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.58,0:19:48.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I thought he'd keep his promise to quit smoking.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.04,0:19:52.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Sudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was madly in love with Ena.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.67,0:19:55.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's assume - and this is just an assumption...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.09,0:20:00.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if I knew that Gouki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was secretly smoking...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.80,0:20:03.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the way here, he called me on the phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.34,0:20:08.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I said in front of everyone that if he didn't\Nstop smoking our engagement was off.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.47,0:20:14.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you think I could predict that he'd go against that\Nand get out of the car with a cigarette in his mouth?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.06,0:20:17.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even after I told him not to smoke?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.90,0:20:19.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just as she said.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.40,0:20:23.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeing that she told him not to smoke in front of everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.24,0:20:27.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It will be hard to prove that she's the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.58,0:20:29.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, the cigarette didn't start the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.25,0:20:34.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whether he stopped smoking or not, I can't tell...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.50,0:20:38.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, for today at least, I don't think he was smoking inside his car.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.21,0:20:41.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the Professor stopped him...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.72,0:20:45.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went up to the driver's side too, and there was no smell of cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.55,0:20:49.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, how did the fire in the garage start?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.60,0:20:52.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm still not sure about that, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.73,0:20:56.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I am sure that Ena{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is the one who set it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.07,0:21:01.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Try to remember...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.15,0:21:09.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the start, when Inspector Yuminaga said the cause of the\Nfire was his smoking, Ena{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} flared up at him while crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.41,0:21:12.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gouki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said he had quit smoking!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.29,0:21:16.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yet, only a little while after those\Nwords came out of her mouth...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.75,0:21:21.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As a response to me pointing out how it was strange\Nthat there were no opened cigarette packs around...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.76,0:21:26.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Couldn't he have thrown it out the car\Nwindow before he went into the garage?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.89,0:21:30.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she had really believed that he'd quit smoking...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.85,0:21:33.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't she normally have agreed with what I said?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.98,0:21:37.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"It's just like I thought. He did quit smoking."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.73,0:21:38.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.19,0:21:40.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.69,0:21:45.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her inconsistent words all add up if they're from the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.82,0:21:47.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her flare up at Inspector Yuminaga was saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.99,0:21:52.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I didn't know he was secretly smoking!"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.87,0:21:54.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While her objection to me was.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.58,0:21:59.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The cause of the fire was most definitely the lit cigarette."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.71,0:22:02.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that Ena{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.46,0:22:05.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wants, at all costs, for this to look like\Nan accidental death due to smoking.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.09,0:22:08.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, it wasn't an accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.89,0:22:11.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fire was set up on purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.39,0:22:14.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, don't they say, "There can't be smoke without fire"?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.35,0:22:17.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what I'm thinking about right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.56,0:22:20.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's got to be something here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.02,0:22:26.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some trick to starting that fire in the garage without using a detonator.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.76,0:24:17.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.56,0:24:19.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wool Sweater
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.93,0:24:21.31,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Ah, there's a fuzzball on your sweater.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.35,0:24:22.23,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That's because it's wool.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.27,0:24:23.60,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Ah, there's a price tag on your sweater.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.60,0:24:24.65,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That's because it's on sale.
